As used in sections 485h–1 to 485h–5 of this title, the term “long-term contract” shall mean any contract the term of which is more than ten years.
(July 2, 1956, ch. 492, § 3, 70 Stat. 484.)

Editorial Notes
Codification
Section was not enacted as part of the Reclamation Project Act of 1939 which comprises this subchapter.</akn:p></akn:content></akn:section></akn:body></akn:act></akn:akomaNtoso>